<figureCitation box="[764,942,757,781]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Figure 2C, H, I</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[964,989,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">L.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, 2013" authorityName="Asenjo &amp; Ribeiro-Costa" authorityYear="2013" box="[996,1103,757,781]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mery" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis box="[1005,1023,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1048,1103,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">mery</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[143,230,790,813]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[545,570,790,813]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">L.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scheerpeltz" authorityYear="1951" box="[579,735,789,813]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunganus" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis box="[588,606,790,813]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[633,735,790,813]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">yunganus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[796,821,790,813]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">L.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[830,1022,789,813]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zischkaianus" subGenus="Tropiochirus">
(
<emphasis box="[839,857,790,813]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[884,1022,789,813]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">zischkaianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the first dorsal tooth of the left mandible not bifurcate (
<figureCitation box="[725,843,821,845]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1269" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[143,369,926,988]" box="[143,270,926,949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">
<heading box="[143,270,926,949]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[143,270,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[143,369,926,988]" box="[143,369,964,988]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">BL: 12.48, BW: 2.06</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[143,857,1028,1052]" box="[143,857,1028,1052]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Body strongly depressed. Body all black except tarsi red-brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[143,1104,1092,1435]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[143,211,1092,1116]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Head.</emphasis>
Transverse (
<figureCitation box="[352,471,1092,1116]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
). Inner lateral teeth separated by a depression extending to base. Inner and outer lateral teeth fused and resembling a septum; median sulcus deep, gradually narrowing anteriorly; laterofrontal depressions oval. Labrum with outer edge strongly angled and lateral-apical edge concave. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[968,1098,1187,1211]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Figures 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[143,176,1219,1243]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">3C</figureCitation>
) with lateral longitudinal ridge occupying less than two-thirds of apical region; external margin developed, attenuated anteriorly. Left mandible (
<figureCitation box="[873,988,1251,1275]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
) with first dorsal tooth developed, straight and not bifurcate, accessory tooth near lateral longitudinal ridge; second dorsal tooth little developed and resembling a small hill; first ventral tooth with tooth accessory, third ventral tooth consisting of two structures not fused at the base. Submentum with setae arranged in row on the anterolateral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[143,1104,1474,1690]" lastBlockId="13.[211,1172,167,255]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1269" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[143,233,1474,1498]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[375,495,1474,1498]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="1268">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
) a little wider than long (PL: 2.21, LP: 2.42); superior marginal line of hypomeron not interrupted, not bent to dorsal region at anterior margin and slightly bent to region at posterior margin; without a pair of small depressions near basal constriction. Inferior marginal line of hypomeron reaching anterior margin. Apex of prosternal process strongly expanded and resembling a circular plate, extending considerably beyond the lateral process of hypomeron. Metaventrite with microsculpture longitudinally undulate in median region and without small longitudinal median depression near posterior edge. Mesoscutellum with apex rounded. Elytra longer than broad and without pair of small depressions on posterior-lateral edge (EL: 2.67, EW: 2.21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[211,1172,311,430]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,322,311,335]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Cylindrical. Sternite III with keel of apex rounded. Tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[1049,1163,311,335]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Figure 4P</figureCitation>
) sclerotized with left and right plates separated, each with five or six setae of various lengths. Tergite X (
<figureCitation box="[421,533,375,399]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Figure 4P</figureCitation>
) membranous except for sclerotized apical part, with two pairs of long apical setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[211,1172,486,701]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">
<emphasis box="[211,276,486,510]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Male.</emphasis>
Sternite IX (
<figureCitation box="[419,535,486,510]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Figure 4Q</figureCitation>
) composed of two plates, distal plate sclerotized, anterior margin slightly projecting, posterior margin with small acute projection in the middle and with two long setae; proximal plate less sclerotized, greater than apical, broadened in middle and with angle at posterior border not projecting. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1164,582,606]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Figure 4M–O</figureCitation>
) with median lobe slightly bulbous at base, almost straight at apex, weakly sclerotized on dorsal side and a small plate sclerotized on ventral side; parameres short, pointed and fused dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[211,1172,757,845]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">
<emphasis box="[211,297,757,781]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male, except for the gonocoxites divided longitudinally (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1159,757,781]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="13" pageNumber="1269">Figure 4R</figureCitation>
). The distal plate with apex membranous and long seta; proximal plate with the posterior region rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
